Foot and mouth disease, Russia
------------------------
Information received on 18 Jun 2013 from Dr Evgeny Nepoklonov, Deputy Head, Federal Service for Veterinary and Phytosanitary Surveillance, Ministry of Agriculture, Moscow, Russia

Summary
Report type: Follow-up report No. 1
Date of start of the event: 3 Jun 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 8 Jun 2013
Report date: 18 Jun 2013
Date submitted to OIE: 18 Jun 2013
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 29 May 2013
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: A
Nature of diagnosis: Suspicion, Clinical, Laboratory (basic), Laboratory (advanced), Necropsy
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (2)
Outbreak 1: Cossack village Pregradnaya, Urupsky raion, Karachayevo-Cherkesskaya Resp.
Date of start of the outbreak: 13 Jun 2013
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Village
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 296 / 40 / 5 / - / -

Outbreak 2: Rural community Solenoye, Mostovsky raion, Krasnodarskiy Kray
Date of start of the outbreak: 15 Jun 2013
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Village
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 161 / 4 / - / - / -

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 2
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 457 / 44 / 5 / - / -
Outbreak statistics
Species Apparent / morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 9.63 percent / ** / ** / **
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter
**Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive; Contact with wild species

Epidemiological comments:
1. Outbreak in Krasnodarskiy Kray: The outbreak is in the buffer zone with vaccination against FMD. It is located 5 km from Karachayevo-Cherkesskaya Republic, where the FMD infected area is located.
2. Outbreak in Karachayevo-Cherkesskaya Republic: The outbreak is in the buffer zone with vaccination against FMD. It is 3 km from the 1st outbreak reported on 3 Jun 2013. The distance from the outbreak to the border with Georgia is 60 km. Wild, cloven-hoofed animals could be the possible source of infection.

Control measures
Measures applied: Quarantine, Movement control inside the country, Screening, Disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s), Modified stamping out, No vaccination, No treatment of affected animals.

Measures to be applied: Vaccination in response to the outbreak(s).

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type:

1. FGBU "Federal Centre for Animal Health" (National laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / indirect fluorescent antibody (IFA) test / 17 Jun 2013 / Positive

2. FGBI "Federal Centre for Animal Health" (FGBI "ARRIAH") (OIE's Reference Laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / complement fixation test (CFT) / 17 Jun 2013 / Positive
Cattle / nested RT-PCR / 8 Jun 2013 / Positive
Cattle / nucleotide sequencing / 17 Jun 2013 / Positive
Cattle / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 17 Jun 2013 / Positive

